<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 02 at 4:52PM CDT  by NWS Knoxville</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Bradley
and southeastern Hamilton Counties through 630 PM EDT...
At 551 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Cleveland, moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Chattanooga, Cleveland, South Cleveland, Harrison, East Cleveland,
Wildwood Lake, Collegedale, Waterville, Hopewell and Harrison Bay
State Park.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
